P4ML Static Thought Leadership Site (OMIC-Assist Initiative)

This repository contains the front-end code for the P4ML static marketing and thought leadership website, designed to communicate the strategic vision, national alignment, and technical depth of the OMIC-Assist research initiative.

ðŸŽ¯ Strategic Objective

The website is engineered to instantly convey P4ML's credibility within the UAE health innovation ecosystem by highlighting:

National Alignment: Explicit partnership with the Ministry of Economy's Future100 initiative and alignment with DHA health goals.

Scale and Vision: The unprecedented scope of the OMIC-Assist Study (2M+ participants).

Technical Leverage: Strategic partnerships with core technology providers (Evsop, Seqbiome) and the integration of multi-omic data.

âœ¨ Key Features

The website is built as a single-page application (index.html) using a modern, mobile-first aesthetic (Tailwind CSS style) to ensure a clean, executive-ready presentation across all devices.

Featured Partnerships:

Government & Clinical: Dubai Health Authority (DHA), Fakeeh University Hospital.

Technical Ecosystem: Evsop (Biopharma Solutions), Seqbiome (Microbiome Sequencing).

Key Initiatives:

Triple Helix Model: Explicit collaboration between industry, academia, and government.

Training Center of Excellence: Commitment to regional knowledge transfer and job creation.

